premise_source_doc_sentence: The epithets `` black-legged '' and `` red-legged '' are used to distinguish the two species in North America , but in Europe , where R. brevirostris is not found , the black-legged kittiwake is often known simply as kittiwake , or more colloquially in some areas as tickleass or tickleace .

The kittiwakes  (  genus Rissa  )  are two closely related seabird species in the gull family Laridae , the black-legged kittiwake  (  R. tridactyla  )  and the red-legged kittiwake  (  R. brevirostris  )  .
Tardigrades  (  -LSB- ˈtɑrdᵻˌgreɪd -RSB- also known as water bears , space bears , or moss piglets  )  are water-dwelling , eight-legged , segmented micro-animals .

In addition to some other finds from the Cretaceous and the Cambrian period , Beorn is one of the few references to the existence of tardigrades in the history of the earth , and its largely modern appearance shows that tardigrades have changed only slightly over the last 65 million years .
The genus name Rissa is from the Icelandic name Rita for the black-legged kittiwake .
